          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Higher Education",
          "E-Learning",
          "Knowledge-tracing-driven personalized recommender / AI copilot for educational resource allocation; combines BKT-style mastery estimation, signal processing, convex optimization, and generative AI chatbot delivery",
          "Personalized next-step learning support: educational resources, review materials, learning activities, reminders, Q&A help, and adaptive intervention guidance",
          "203 university students in a controlled study; 4 experimental groups of 40–41 students plus 40 in control",
          "University AI course; also implemented on programming-learning platforms My Code Weapon and Nemobot",
          "Assignment submissions, quiz/exam responses, participation logs, platform activity, chatbot queries, feedback surveys, OJ submission data (scores, attempts, errors, timestamps, resource usage)",
          "Student state initialized through BKT-based mastery probability P(Lj,i)P(L_{j,i})P(Lj,i) using submission histories and contextual features; policy parameters optimized for personalized resource allocation; chatbot uses these outputs to deliver recommendations",
          "Iterative flywheel: new signals are smoothed and aggregated, mastery is updated in real time, recommendations are regenerated, and model/policy parameters are refined continuously",
          "Signals treated as time-series; multimodal analytics pipeline includes smoothing, normalization, sampling, feature embedding, and multimodal aggregation; in OJ setting, verdicts, error types, execution time, memory, attempts, difficulty, and timestamps are used",
          "Resource recommendation, proactive reminders, conversational question handling, tailored learning activities, foundational vs advanced exercise suggestions",
          "Controlled study: COTUTOR achieved highest assignment score (73.2%), post-course survey score (72.8%), activity participation rate (73.9%), and prediction accuracy (67.4%) versus control, BKT, DKT, and Code-DKT. Compared with control, assignment score improved from 68.4% to 73.2%",
          "It operationalizes KT into resource allocation and chatbot-delivered recommendations. The chatbot screenshots on page 12 help make the recommendation role concrete",
          "Recommendation effects are shown through group outcomes, but the paper does not isolate which specific recommendation type produced the gains; one-course university study; some effects versus stronger baselines are modest; framework is broader than a classical item recommender"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 8
    },
    {
      "block_id": "3394750c-f3ba-804d-83ad-fa2a2e3b7e24",
