        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "ITS",
          "Next Exercise is Correct",
          "Correct vs Incorrect; mastery probability P(Lj,i)P(L_{j,i})P(Lj,i)",
          "EdNet KT1 subset from 784,000+ students\n\n",
          "TOEIC preparation in Santa ITS (benchmark setting)",
          "Santa ITS (benchmark setting)EdNet KT1 interaction logs + metadata + skill labels / Q-matrix",
          "Timestamped interaction sequences, user/item IDs, answers, skill labels, smoothed contextual features, submission/performance signals",
          "Traditional BKT is interpretable but limited; DKT handles temporal complexity but is less interpretable and data-hungry; existing systems often do not integrate richer learning signals for real-time adaptivity",
          "COTUTOR extends BKT with signal processing and convex-optimization-based updating/planning, integrating smoothed multimodal learning signals for more adaptive and interpretable KT",
          "Remove duplicates; remove missing user answers; remove items with undefined skill tags; construct binary Q-matrix from metadata; filter students with fewer than 10 interactions; exponential smoothing applied to contextual signals",
          "BKT, DKT, Code-DKT, COTUTOR",
          "Holdout Method",
          "{Accuracy: 0.843 - COTUTOR, AUC: 0.717 - COTUTOR, PR-AUC: 0.741  - COTUTOR, RMSE: 0.229  - COTUTOR, NLL: 0.594  - COTUTOR}",
          "benchmarks learning-state estimation against KT baselines on EdNet. Best gains are clearest in Accuracy, RMSE, and NLL; AUC/PR-AUC gains over baselines are smaller but still best overall",
          "Exact benchmark subset size is not fully specified; COTUTOR is not a pure KT model only, but a larger AI-assisted framework; comparison is limited to a small set of baselines"
        ]
      ],
